cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks and defenses in deep neural networks that handle 3D data, specifically point clouds. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the unique structure of 3D point clouds and proposes defenses that exploit this structure, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. Finally, the paper deals with the security aspect of deep neural networks, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
